# Backend Architecture Rule (FastAPI)

- Backend root is `backend/app`, keep strict layering: `api` -> `services` -> `repositories` -> `models`.
- Route modules live under `app/api/endpoints/`; aggregate them in `app/api/router.py` (mounted in `main.py` with prefix `settings.api_prefix`).
- API endpoints only handle validation/response; business logic must stay in `services`, DB access in `repositories`.
- Keep authentication dependencies in `app/api/deps/auth.py`; prefer `Authorization: Bearer <token>`.
- Keep shared constants in `app/constants/` (`enums.py`, `error_codes.py`); avoid magic strings/numbers.
- All custom errors must use `app/core/exceptions.py`; HTTP error bodies are built in `app/core/exception_handlers.py` (`error_json_response`).
- Register middleware and exception handlers centrally (`setup_middleware`, `register_exception_handlers`), app lifecycle via `lifespan`.
- Database session management must use `app/db/session.py`; avoid creating ad-hoc engines/sessions in business code.
- Models inherit from `app/models/base.py::ModelBase`; soft delete uses `deleted_at` (not `is_deleted`).
- New config keys must be added to `app/core/config.py` and reflected in `backend/.env.example`.
- HTTP API is mounted under `/api` (no `/v1`/`v2` path prefix); handle breaking changes with migrations, feature flags, or coordinated client updates as needed.
- Prefer small, focused modules; avoid building all-in-one DAL/framework-like abstractions.

## Example

```python
# ✅ Good: endpoint delegates business logic
@router.post("/login")
async def login(payload: LoginRequest, db: AsyncSession = Depends(get_db)):
    return await auth_service.login(db, payload)
```
